Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.28,0:29:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they have no guidance towards truth and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.60,0:29:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people, there are cultures where if you don't cheat the customer, you get beaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.89,0:29:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't cheat the customer, you get beaten when you get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.25,0:29:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No cultures are built that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.79,0:29:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.26,0:29:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next slide, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.26,0:29:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the evolution of consciousness over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.65,0:29:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see that the level and percentage of elapsed time, that it's only very recently,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.71,0:29:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only very, very recently that mankind suddenly evolved in a very forward, upward direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.79,0:29:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So mankind throughout most of history then,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.79,0:29:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,was extremely primitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.96,0:29:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There are large parts of the world where man is still primitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.56,0:30:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Large parts of the world where people are still extremely primitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.30,0:30:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea that you serve God by killing your fellow human beings is a current dumb idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.60,0:30:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you please God is by killing people who don't think the way you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.27,0:30:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.27,0:30:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And where that prevails dominates very important pieces of culture in the world today.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.31,0:30:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,These earth epics, we have your earth epics and the amount of time that's going by.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.96,0:30:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you can see, the earth epics then have, you might say, speeded up.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.99,0:30:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.15,0:30:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't care about earth epics at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.15,0:30:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds too scholastic, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.15,0:30:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to stay simple so that we can all comprehend what we're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.78,0:31:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So to keep it simple, I love animals because animals keep it simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.32,0:31:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the animals exhibit these various qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.32,0:31:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Various wonderful qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.32,0:31:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we left the dog at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.46,0:31:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, where is Kelsey calibrated?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.46,0:31:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to calibrate Kelsey.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.46,0:31:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She's over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.46,0:31:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 300.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.46,0:31:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She's over 250.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.00,0:31:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,245.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.60,0:31:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelsey's over 240.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.05,0:31:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The doggy at home, my dog calibrates at 240.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.08,0:31:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog calibrates at 240.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.78,0:31:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And where do we say mankind rated?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.32,0:32:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safer with our doggy than most of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.23,0:32:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.23,0:32:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog loves.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.01,0:32:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog appreciates kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.01,0:32:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a charitable person.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.01,0:32:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Is attracted to goodness, truth, and beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.15,0:32:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.15,0:32:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.66,0:32:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, that's very interesting, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.00,0:32:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That animals calibrate higher than a large percentage of the human population.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.61,0:32:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to get depressed about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.86,0:32:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't go there where they live.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.86,0:32:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get on a plane with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.93,0:32:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.93,0:32:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you have to take your shoes off?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.48,0:32:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to take your shoes off to get on an airplane because somebody who calibrates less
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.77,0:33:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,than my dog is not bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.68,0:33:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to just worry about their shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.68,0:33:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to try and keep a straight face.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.50,0:33:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I have to worry about what they got in their shorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.50,0:33:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.55,0:33:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What a great job.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.96,0:33:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.99,0:33:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What a great job.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.99,0:33:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be a shorts inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.23,0:33:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, a shorts inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.64,0:33:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.64,0:34:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad our guards checked everybody's shorts on the way into this auditorium tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.72,0:34:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The shorts inspector have checked you all out.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.80,0:34:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.80,0:34:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the animal kingdom then, where is the doggy?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.05,0:34:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.23,0:34:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the dog's wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.23,0:34:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,500.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.23,0:34:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So Kelsey's tail on his wagon is 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.59,0:34:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And a kitty's purr is 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.32,0:34:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So animals are capable of exhibiting and feeling and returning love.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.71,0:34:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So we won't put down the animal kingdom anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.73,0:34:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing as dogs and cats calibrate higher than a large percentage of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.28,0:34:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.40,0:35:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a shock, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.40,0:35:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have at home a parrot.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.23,0:35:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What's her name?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.11,0:35:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.59,0:35:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli speaks English.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.59,0:35:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell her what your parrot is saying recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.75,0:35:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Call my lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.75,0:35:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things that the bird knows Susan's taught her.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.03,0:35:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The bird, I mean, Susan has such a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.03,0:35:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She teaches the bird all these funny things.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.03,0:35:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm sitting there watching the news and the bird is saying, call my lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.98,0:36:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's her latest, call my lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.98,0:36:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She always says, mama's not happy, nobody's happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.21,0:36:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If mama's not happy, nobody's happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.78,0:36:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're better off with a pig that calibrates at 205 than many of the people in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.61,0:36:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,who would like to praise you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.61,0:36:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Praise God by blowing you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.80,0:36:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was like that, it'll say, busload of children, busload of 30 children blown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.57,0:36:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it'll name some group, claims credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.57,0:36:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a group, claims credit for blowing up the busload of children.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.57,0:36:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Claims credit, hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.57,0:36:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.57,0:36:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So Oscar the cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.59,0:37:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oscar the famous cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.59,0:37:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oscar is that cat that can tell when somebody is due to die within 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.59,0:37:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You all know about Oscar the cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.59,0:37:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You all know about Oscar the cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.32,0:37:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ew, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.48,0:37:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.86,0:37:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just want to, I think it's so interesting that the animal kingdom, the animal kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.92,0:37:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it shows the evolution of consciousness from the beginning right up to the highest levels of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.92,0:37:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So man actually calibrates lower than a lot of the animals on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.21,0:37:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't trust an alligator.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.48,0:37:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People are always fighting alligators.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.48,0:37:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Alligator fighters, alligators only calibrate at 45.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.11,0:37:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So people put their head in the mouth of an alligator.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.50,0:37:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Need a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.50,0:37:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They think it's a well-trained alligator.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.63,0:38:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The alligator doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.63,0:38:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The alligator's strategy is we'll do this for about 20 times and then we're going to have dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.11,0:38:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The alligator has you planned for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.34,0:38:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When an alligator invites you for dinner, he means he's going to have you for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.30,0:38:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.46,0:38:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.46,0:38:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to give us an overall context.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.46,0:38:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,An overall context of reality and how it has evolved up through the Komodo dragon, alligators, dinosaurs, whales, dolphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.84,0:38:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And dolphins are at 95.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.92,0:38:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.23,0:38:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.23,0:38:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Any questions about the animals or is that enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.23,0:38:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough about animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.23,0:38:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.23,0:38:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go on to more interesting things.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.23,0:39:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.30,0:39:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world came out of the University of Chicago and are extremely well known around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.07,0:39:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Great books of the Western world then recalibrate the intellectual foundation of Western society and the evolution of Western society.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.96,0:39:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And just for reference, some of these things are just good to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.11,0:39:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristotle calibrates at 500, 498, 498.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.48,0:39:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristotle.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.82,0:39:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Chaucer at 480.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.82,0:39:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Copernicus at 455.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.07,0:39:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin, the evolution of the species, calibrates at 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.07,0:39:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwinism.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.63,0:39:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes at 490.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.63,0:39:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dostoevsky, 465.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.63,0:40:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Engels, 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.82,0:40:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.13,0:40:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was Engels' co-worker?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.13,0:40:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.61,0:40:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did Engels work with?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.61,0:40:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.03,0:40:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Karl Marx, 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.26,0:40:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl Marx calibrates at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.44,0:40:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we understand why the far left calibrates low.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.71,0:40:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the closer you get to Marxism, the lower the calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.09,0:40:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Marxism has been tried in several major countries, and it resulted in the starvation of 100 million people in one country and 10 million in another.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.44,0:41:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't have much sympathy for Marxist concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.73,0:41:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very good to know this is the background of Western culture as we know it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.98,0:41:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Immanuel Kant, Kepler, Herman Melville.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.32,0:41:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that an interesting list of people?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.05,0:41:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Plato at 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.05,0:41:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when I grew up, we adolescents were sort of intellectuals, I guess, according to local standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.19,0:41:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we used to study Plato and discuss Plato and Socrates while other kids, I guess, were playing stickball or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.32,0:41:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what they were doing out there, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.32,0:41:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Adam Smith, Sophocles, Tolstoy, Virgil.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.32,0:41:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Any question about the great books of the Western world?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.61,0:41:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great thing to know of.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.61,0:42:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, it came out of the University of Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.19,0:42:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what year it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.19,0:42:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.19,0:42:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are whole universities.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.19,0:42:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There are universities whose name I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.51,0:42:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the curriculum consists solely of...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.51,0:42:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It consists solely of studying the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.46,0:42:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the name of the university.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.90,0:42:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world is the curriculum.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.13,0:42:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Having studied them, you are more educated than people who go to ordinary universities,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.13,0:42:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which teach a great deal of things that are not particularly intellectual of great value.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.19,0:42:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The average university today...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.65,0:42:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.65,0:42:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The average public university today...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.65,0:42:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates over 200, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.65,0:42:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The average public university, supported by your taxes,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.57,0:43:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 200, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.57,0:43:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The average university, supported by your taxes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.55,0:43:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,where you send your children to be educated,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.55,0:43:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 200, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.71,0:43:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The average university in the United States does not even calibrate over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.25,0:43:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All your hard-earned books to send them off to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.46,0:43:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you send them off to school, they calibrate high and they're bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.11,0:43:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when they come home again, you realize they have gone down,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.88,0:43:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,have become some kind of strange phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.42,0:43:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because they've been brainwashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.05,0:43:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a book called Indoctrination.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.05,0:43:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Indoctrination U.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.05,0:43:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Explains the phenomena in our current world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.36,0:43:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The world can go to hell in a handbasket if it wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.36,0:44:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no objection.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.80,0:44:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to send your kids off to become educated idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.80,0:44:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no objection to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.11,0:44:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.40,0:44:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you should be aware of what it is you are doing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.40,0:44:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and what the consequences are.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.40,0:44:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think I did write about this phenomena in some recent book.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.40,0:44:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.55,0:44:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so Marxism at 130 then explains the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.55,0:44:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the low calibration below the low.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.55,0:44:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of reality explains why when it's tried in a country,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.55,0:44:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the country goes into starvation and the economy collapses.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.55,0:44:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.98,0:44:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is the functions of the brain, left brain and right brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.40,0:45:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that below 200, you have the animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.84,0:45:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, you have left brain dominance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.96,0:45:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Stress results in fight or flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.96,0:45:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The release of adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.15,0:45:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Alarm reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.15,0:45:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It releases killer cells into the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.80,0:45:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a thymic test.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.80,0:45:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.80,0:45:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want to straighten out your energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.80,0:45:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,which has gotten reversed by bad energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.01,0:45:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,by bad circumstances, bad environment, whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.05,0:45:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you say to yourself, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.05,0:45:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called the thymic film.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.94,0:45:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think of something, someone you love, it's even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.44,0:45:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think about Susie and I think, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.80,0:45:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.84,0:45:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I now calibrate up over 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.84,0:46:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,600.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.26,0:46:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I calibrate over 600, 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.61,0:46:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.61,0:46:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You should tell everyone what you're calibrating at on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.00,0:46:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.00,0:46:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.00,0:46:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.00,0:46:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.07,0:46:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.07,0:46:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The thymic thump is how you recover from your energy being blown out
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.07,0:46:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,by something very negative happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.07,0:46:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So below 200, then, the left brain dominates.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.90,0:46:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Stress releases adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.90,0:46:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The fight or flight phenomena disrupts the acupuncture meridians
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.28,0:46:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and results in disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.28,0:46:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So negative thinking and negative environments, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.48,0:46:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually lead to activation of the disease process.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.48,0:46:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Disease process.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.48,0:46:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People want to know, how can I get well?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.48,0:47:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you do the opposite of what leads you over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.48,0:47:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Above 200, the emotion of being loving towards everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.40,0:47:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace and lovingness release endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.11,0:47:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It releases the killer cells that kill off diseases.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.28,0:47:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Increases immunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.28,0:47:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Increases healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.28,0:47:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Balances the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.28,0:47:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get a positive muscle test response,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.28,0:47:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the test that we do with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.28,0:47:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you try to stay in a positive environment
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.71,0:47:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,with a positive attitude and let go of negativity
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.71,0:47:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has a deleterious effect physiologically
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.71,0:47:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as psychological and emotional.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.82,0:47:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.82,0:47:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.82,0:47:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.53,0:47:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The cause of social problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.53,0:48:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all kinds of theories of what causes social problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.53,0:48:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we correlate the levels of consciousness and social problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.53,0:48:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that what accounts for unemployment,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.57,0:48:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,poverty, happiness, and criminality,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.73,0:48:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things are explained, not by sociologic phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.05,0:48:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Cleaning up the neighborhood, let's say, should get rid of criminality.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.07,0:48:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.07,0:48:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.07,0:48:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.55,0:48:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So the level of consciousness is 600 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.55,0:48:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.55,0:48:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.55,0:48:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.71,0:48:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.71,0:48:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,As the level of consciousness goes down,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.11,0:48:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for the 400s to the 500s,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.96,0:48:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the rate of unemployment is 2%.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.96,0:48:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Rate of poverty is 0.5%.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.19,0:49:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is 70%.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.51,0:49:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And criminality is, again, very small, 2%.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.80,0:49:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the higher the level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.80,0:49:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the more these phenomena become positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.15,0:49:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.15,0:49:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is the main determinant of what we consider to be social problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.15,0:49:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty is not due to poverty-ism.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.53,0:49:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's people with a low level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.92,0:49:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are prone to poverty.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.44,0:49:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People with a higher level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.44,0:49:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,will become successful no matter where you put them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.69,0:49:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you put me in a poverty neighborhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.69,0:49:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to find out what poverty people buy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.69,0:49:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and start selling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.71,0:49:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the criminal does.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.71,0:49:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They like heroin, so we'll sell heroin, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.82,0:49:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll go on to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.82,0:49:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And correlational levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.32,0:50:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.51,0:50:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,100% of enlightened people are happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.90,0:50:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,100 people who came...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.90,0:50:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,100% of people calibrated over 600, the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.05,0:50:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 590% of the people are happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.05,0:50:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest are kooks of some kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.86,0:50:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,People dominated by a reason, 80% are happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.88,0:50:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,People dominated by neutrality, 60% are happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.17,0:50:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,People dominated by courage, 55% are happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.34,0:50:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So the higher levels of consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.63,0:50:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,are correlated with greater satisfaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.63,0:50:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasure, and happiness in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.63,0:50:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and a much lower arrest rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.30,0:50:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not likely to end up on welfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.30,0:50:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, dominated, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.61,0:50:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,by the lesser levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.61,0:50:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see that the number of people who are happy
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.61,0:51:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes lower and lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.78,0:51:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Prideful people are...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.78,0:51:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride goes before a fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.78,0:51:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Angry people, we all avoid angry people.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.78,0:51:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are addicted to cravingness and desiringness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.78,0:51:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,People that are dominated by fear, grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.78,0:51:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here, apathy and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.94,0:51:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.94,0:51:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And we said the way to get off guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.19,0:51:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is stop being egocentric.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.19,0:51:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody cares about your guilt except you,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.19,0:51:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.19,0:51:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time you feel guilty, just say,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.55,0:51:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that's just egocentricity and I don't need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.25,0:51:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of guilt, just learn to do better.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.25,0:51:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of being condemning towards people,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.25,0:51:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,become forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.25,0:51:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to feel guilty about condemning them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.67,0:51:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, there we go, the next level.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.67,0:51:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.53,0:51:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.23,0:52:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,People very often write us about spiritual teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.23,0:52:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and we get a lot of emails and mail about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.23,0:52:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.23,0:52:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we listed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.23,0:52:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't the complete list, but it's quite a few.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.36,0:52:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It covers 90% of the great spiritual teachers in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.36,0:52:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,More than 90%.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.80,0:52:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Great teachers of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.84,0:52:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And we list what their level,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.84,0:52:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness that they represent.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.84,0:52:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.84,0:52:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Aurobindo Black Elk.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.84,0:52:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacob Bohm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.36,0:52:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Swami Bhutananda.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.36,0:52:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Eric Butterworth.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.36,0:52:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Kelvin Confucius.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.36,0:52:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dalai Lama.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.63,0:52:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,All these people represent truth of various levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.63,0:52:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's useful primarily for orientation, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.63,0:52:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for orientation,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.71,0:52:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can tell where you are
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.92,0:52:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in your own belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.92,0:53:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.67,0:53:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Nisargadatta Maharaj.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.03,0:53:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I always liked Nisargadatta.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.03,0:53:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I like that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.03,0:53:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to have another name.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.03,0:53:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You can call me Nisargadatta if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.38,0:53:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate to 720.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.38,0:53:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.38,0:53:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll last this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.63,0:53:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.80,0:53:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual teachers continued.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.80,0:53:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's a lot of them, aren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.86,0:53:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have listed in some of our books,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.86,0:53:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and we just re-present it here for the reminder
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.86,0:53:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have calibrated all the great teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.86,0:53:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.86,0:53:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.86,0:53:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a practical, pragmatic usefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.05,0:53:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Alan Watts, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.05,0:53:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and Sri Yukteswar.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.44,0:53:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.44,0:53:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That covers the great majority of questions
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.55,0:54:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that we get have to do with various spiritual teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.55,0:54:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and whether that person calibrates well.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.55,0:54:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, what we mean by well is over 200, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.55,0:54:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some well-known spiritual teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.76,0:54:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but they do not calibrate over 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.96,0:54:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and we won't mention them.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.59,0:54:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.32,0:54:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,People question divinity of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.32,0:54:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The great avatars, the great spiritual teachers of all time,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.32,0:54:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all collectively calibrate around 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.96,0:54:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,On our scale of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.96,0:54:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ at 1,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.96,0:54:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha at 1,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.96,0:54:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna at 1,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.96,0:54:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Zoroaster at 1,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.96,0:54:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the Apostles,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.15,0:54:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of God is Om,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.57,0:54:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,John the Baptist,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.82,0:54:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses, Abraham,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.82,0:54:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Paul,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.44,0:54:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Muhammad after, before, and after age,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.67,0:55:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,certain age, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.67,0:55:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so this really confirms
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.67,0:55:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of spiritual truth
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.67,0:55:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,taught by some of the most famous
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.67,0:55:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and greatest teachers throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.67,0:55:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next one, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.67,0:55:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all about love.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.09,0:55:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is warmth, appreciation,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.09,0:55:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving, inclusive,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.48,0:55:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,cordiality, it's uplifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.76,0:55:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So love is giving, uplifting,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.76,0:55:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,generosity, sharing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.90,0:55:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an inner humility,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.38,0:55:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,gratitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.84,0:55:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and a certain sweetness to love.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.21,0:55:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.63,0:55:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Who could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.42,0:56:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's today's media.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.84,0:56:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Washington, D.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.88,0:56:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolf in sheep clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.48,0:56:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We're here, we're from the government,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.48,0:56:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're here to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.44,0:56:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We're from the government,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.63,0:56:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're here to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.80,0:56:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so illusions versus reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.09,0:56:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So one thing that's useful about
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.09,0:56:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the scale of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.09,0:56:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the calibration technique
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.09,0:56:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you break through illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.40,0:56:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You break through the illusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.40,0:56:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole world can be convinced of something,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.40,0:56:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet your arm tells you that it's otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.05,0:56:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you believe the whole world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.05,0:56:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or your own self?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.07,0:57:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you recheck your technique
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.07,0:57:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and make sure you're correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.50,0:57:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the arm says something,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.50,0:57:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.50,0:57:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and what the world believes is not the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.44,0:57:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, students of this work
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.44,0:57:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are in a unique position.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.44,0:57:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Being sometimes the only people on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.61,0:57:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that really are aware of what the truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.61,0:57:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or have access to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.61,0:57:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, nobody else does.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.05,0:57:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they are persuaded by the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.05,0:57:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the media can be very convincing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.32,0:57:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The media and the politicians
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.32,0:57:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the publicizers
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.38,0:57:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,can be very convincing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.38,0:57:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet somehow they make your arm go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.38,0:57:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's very useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.53,0:57:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great gift to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.53,0:57:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,To be able to tell the level of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.53,0:57:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,whether a thing is real or not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.53,0:57:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand whether...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.30,0:57:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can also say, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.55,0:57:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a good neighborhood to open a hardware store.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.55,0:58:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've got a weak arm, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.55,0:58:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see its pragmatic usefulness
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.82,0:58:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.82,0:58:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a good lady for me to start dating
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.07,0:58:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and going out with.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.07,0:58:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a good gentleman for me to date.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.07,0:58:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.73,0:58:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Useful in every area of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.73,0:58:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal relationships, business, politics,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.73,0:58:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,scientific truth, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.86,0:58:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a current scientific doctrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.86,0:58:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.17,0:58:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth is warming up due to human...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.17,0:58:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,due to human influences.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.17,0:58:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.69,0:58:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You hit me wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.80,0:58:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warming...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.80,0:58:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.80,0:58:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warm...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.80,0:58:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you a different...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.80,0:58:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.88,0:58:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warming is due to the magnetic electrical activity
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.88,0:59:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.88,0:59:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.88,0:59:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.13,0:59:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warming is due to sunspots.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.80,0:59:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.80,0:59:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warming is not due to human activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.05,0:59:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.05,0:59:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.40,0:59:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that is always in the news recurrently, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.63,0:59:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That if you...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.63,0:59:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans can only change their lifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.63,0:59:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,then the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.63,0:59:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the Earth would cool down.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.63,0:59:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know that it has to do with magnetic activity
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.63,0:59:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the surface of the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.63,0:59:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the so-called sunspots.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.84,0:59:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they shoot out zillions of volts
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.92,0:59:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of electric...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.92,0:59:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,electronic radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.92,0:59:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what influences the temperature of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.92,0:59:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.92,0:59:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.17,0:59:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the picture of Earth warming
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.17,0:59:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we just had there before.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.17,0:59:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.69,0:59:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're going to get to the subject for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.71,0:59:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.71,1:00:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What we're going to be talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.28,1:00:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is today.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.28,1:00:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What time is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.40,1:00:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.40,1:00:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.40,1:00:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We have about fifteen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.40,1:00:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.40,1:00:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A break?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.40,1:00:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.59,1:00:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.59,1:00:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.53,1:00:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Pepsi Max, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.53,1:00:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Pepsi used to give me a buzz,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.53,1:00:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but Pepsi Max, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.71,1:00:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I can leap over mountains.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.71,1:00:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What we're talking about today
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.71,1:00:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is we're going to go through the human lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.71,1:00:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from beginning to end,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.96,1:00:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at the stresses,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.96,1:00:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual challenges
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.96,1:00:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.13,1:00:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of human life.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.13,1:00:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to cover
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.13,1:00:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the entire human lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.13,1:01:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and see how best to handle
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.42,1:01:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the various stresses
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.42,1:01:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to which humans are automatically subjected
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.55,1:01:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from the very moment of birth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.55,1:01:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.55,1:01:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the stress.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.28,1:01:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In early life,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.96,1:01:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,birth itself is a sensory overwhelm.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.30,1:01:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I frankly remember my own birth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.30,1:01:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.30,1:01:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the powerful,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.96,1:01:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the powerful contractions
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.96,1:01:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,going down over me.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.96,1:01:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember then emerging
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.96,1:01:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,out of warm darkness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.67,1:01:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and safety and security
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.67,1:01:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,into bright lights.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.57,1:01:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.57,1:01:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the lights were so bright
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.57,1:01:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it was blinding.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.57,1:01:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.57,1:01:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was loud.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.57,1:01:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Voices.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.17,1:01:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The voices of people
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.17,1:01:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,were overwhelmingly loud.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.17,1:01:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The environment was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.17,1:01:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was no longer
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.17,1:01:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.46,1:01:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.46,1:01:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.75,1:01:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.75,1:01:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.75,1:01:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.75,1:01:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.75,1:01:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.75,1:01:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.75,1:01:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.03,1:01:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.03,1:01:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.03,1:02:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.15,1:02:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.15,1:02:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.15,1:02:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.15,1:02:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you're no longer safe
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.00,1:02:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and warm and secure.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.00,1:02:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.53,1:02:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So you start out
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.53,1:02:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,like behind an eight ball.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.53,1:02:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And a negative sensory overwhelm.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.21,1:02:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.21,1:02:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.21,1:02:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you haven't eaten yet
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.21,1:02:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're hungry.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.21,1:02:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.21,1:02:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Noisy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.21,1:02:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The lights are blinding.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.21,1:02:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you go through
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.71,1:02:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,separation anxiety,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.71,1:02:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the emotion of fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.71,1:02:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly you go from
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.71,1:02:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a familiar,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.71,1:02:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,quiet,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.71,1:02:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,dark,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.71,1:02:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,warm place.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.55,1:02:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.55,1:02:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we can assist this delivery
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.76,1:02:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the early life by midwifery
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.94,1:02:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so nowadays
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.40,1:02:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,midwives birth the infant
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.73,1:02:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,child into a warm
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.69,1:02:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,tub of water
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.78,1:02:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a warm tub of water
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.30,1:02:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the first phenomena that happens
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.65,1:02:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as soon as you're born
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.73,1:02:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is the phenomena of imprinting
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.28,1:03:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as soon as you're born
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.84,1:03:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you're surrounded with
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.55,1:03:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you imprint
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.26,1:03:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and that becomes your mother
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.88,1:03:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,this has a profound effect on the rest of your life
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.11,1:03:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because what you imprinted on
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.96,1:03:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is there relatively
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.11,1:03:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,permanently
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.80,1:03:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will always associate that with
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.30,1:03:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,safety and security
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.59,1:03:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in whatever went on
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.80,1:03:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at that moment
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.76,1:03:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or if it was the other way around
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.67,1:03:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,your midwifery was bad and they weren't put in warm water
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.73,1:03:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.98,1:03:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,made to feel secure
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.98,1:03:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to be afraid of every new
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.71,1:03:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,situation
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.59,1:03:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,every new situation
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.34,1:03:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to be afraid of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.11,1:03:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll be afraid of every new situation
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.23,1:03:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a baby duck
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.23,1:03:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I had some fertile duck eggs
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.23,1:03:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,back home when I was a kid in the midwest
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.23,1:03:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and the duck eggs were due to hatch
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.59,1:03:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and so this one
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.59,1:03:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the mother duck got off the eggs
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.59,1:04:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and wouldn't sit on it
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.59,1:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so I took the duck egg
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.96,1:04:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which is ready to hatch any old day
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.96,1:04:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and I stuck it in my pocket
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.96,1:04:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and kept it warm that way
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.96,1:04:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so I kept the duck egg in my pocket
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.96,1:04:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for a couple of days
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.96,1:04:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,finally I could feel the pecking feeling there
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.96,1:04:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ducky wanted out
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.96,1:04:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so I took the little duckling out
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.09,1:04:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and set it down in a nice warm place
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.09,1:04:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought the duckling needed some help getting out of the shell
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.09,1:04:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so I cheated a little
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.09,1:04:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and I cracked the shell with my thumbnail like that
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.19,1:04:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and here's this little wet little duckling
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.19,1:04:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,well the little duckling
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.44,1:04:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I dried him up and warmed him up
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.44,1:04:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and carried him around where it was warm
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.57,1:04:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so the little duckling grew up
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.57,1:04:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,from early life
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.71,1:04:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,right next to my chest
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.71,1:04:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,where I kept it warm under my sweater
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.71,1:04:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or my scarf, whatever
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.71,1:04:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so the duckling's name was Peep Peep
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.73,1:05:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so I would go out in the backyard
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.73,1:05:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I went out in the backyard
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.80,1:05:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the little duckling would come racing across the lawn
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.80,1:05:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Peep Peep Peep Peep Peep Peep Peep Peep Peep Peep Peep Peep Peep
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.80,1:05:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because it thought I was its mother
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.80,1:05:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so what we imprint on then
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.30,1:05:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,then
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.51,1:05:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we tend to hold that as a mother
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.19,1:05:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a very interesting thing to know
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.19,1:05:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so whatever you are strangely attracted to very often
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.61,1:05:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you ask yourself what could I have imprinted on
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.61,1:05:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in early child, in childbirth
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.61,1:05:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so imprinting then lasts a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.63,1:05:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and will always be a very warm source of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.63,1:05:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,so mothers are traditionally
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.59,1:05:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's usually the first person you see is your mom
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.46,1:05:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody else
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.50,1:05:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so the mother has traditionally been
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.50,1:06:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that which sustains
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.78,1:06:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,creates and sustains life
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.78,1:06:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so the mother is greatly revered
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.78,1:06:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in all cultures, especially our culture
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.78,1:06:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,not especially but in all cultures
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.03,1:06:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the mother
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.17,1:06:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,really reigns supreme
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.17,1:06:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the mother is necessary for a few seconds
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.17,1:06:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can get rid of him
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.00,1:06:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks a lot George
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.28,1:06:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,many months later he's off on the other side of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.28,1:06:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with some other bimbo
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.32,1:06:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and his mom
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.84,1:06:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,everything relies on mother
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.84,1:06:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so the mother in our culture
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.05,1:06:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the mother on a certain level is almost divine
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.69,1:06:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to speak against or turn against your mother
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.69,1:06:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and she's extremely unthinkable
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.69,1:06:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and not thinkable
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.19,1:06:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so midwifery tries to overcome
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.19,1:06:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the negative impact
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.26,1:07:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of this you arise with an attitude
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.48,1:07:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,either an optimist or a pessimist
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.71,1:07:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,life is either half empty
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.71,1:07:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or half full
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.71,1:07:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I you see so
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.96,1:07:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the birth phenomena then determines
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.96,1:07:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're going to be an optimist or a pessimist
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.96,1:07:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're going to be secure and feel safe or you're going to feel that life is dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.55,1:07:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see right from birth itself, from the first few hours of life, it already sets your attitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.03,1:07:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a safe world, life is safe, or it's a dangerous world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.59,1:07:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And your whole idea of security, half full or half empty, is life half full or half empty?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.98,1:07:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The optimist versus the pessimist.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.71,1:07:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So here this attitude is already set practically after birth.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.94,1:08:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.94,1:08:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then after the birth phenomena comes childhood itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.73,1:08:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What has been your experience of affection?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.30,1:08:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What has been your experience of trust?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.61,1:08:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what has been your experience of siblings and rivalry?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.39,1:08:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,To be an only child is much different than being one of two children,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.21,1:08:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is much different than being...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.36,1:08:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,being one of three, which is much different than being one of five.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.52,1:08:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing that sets our attitudes is the kind of discipline involved.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.96,1:08:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people use positive discipline, other people use negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.56,1:08:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Our sense of confidence arises out of our childhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.21,1:08:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If you got strokes, for being good and productive, or whether you were just ignored.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.80,1:08:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So this whole idea of good versus bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.88,1:09:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're a good person, whether life is good, or you're a bad person, life is bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.25,1:09:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Having bad circumstances at birth very often leads to the chronic criminals.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.06,1:09:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Life has been bad from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.47,1:09:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad mothering, bad environment, bad companions, bad energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.85,1:09:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing that really influences us considerably is birth order.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.30,1:09:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you the oldest of all, the youngest of all, the middle child?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.27,1:09:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.61,1:09:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.81,1:09:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.92,1:09:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.10,1:09:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Traditionally, certain phenomena happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.35,1:09:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're the oldest child, or if you're the youngest one, what the birth order is.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.77,1:09:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing that sets up our attitudes is our experiences.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.64,1:09:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Our experiences in schooling.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.22,1:09:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Our experiences in religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.22,1:09:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Our knowledge and awareness of having a soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.78,1:09:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity for reverence and for spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.85,1:10:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The preoccupation with heaven or hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.92,1:10:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.52,1:10:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really energized by the desire to move to heaven?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.81,1:10:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it merely a fear of hell?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.06,1:10:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So sin and guilt then bring up all the whole fears of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.32,1:10:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Parenting skills then and bringing these things across to the child.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.59,1:10:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And the physical health and heredity are profound factors in influencing our...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.89,1:10:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Our attitudes throughout all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.48,1:10:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reason we're looking at these things is because these are life...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.97,1:10:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,These are life attitudes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.97,1:10:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody sitting out here in the audience right now has been profoundly interested by all these things in their life.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.97,1:10:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And a self-aware person looks at all these various phenomena in their life and comes to a certain understanding about why they are the way they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.15,1:10:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Does everybody here know why they are the way they are?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.52,1:10:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody don't know why they are the way they are?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.01,1:11:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know why they are the way they are?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.46,1:11:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd you go?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.46,1:11:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.46,1:11:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.39,1:11:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you need a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.39,1:11:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.09,1:11:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where the psychiatrist comes in.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.09,1:11:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,To help us to adjust to the phenomena that we don't seem to be able to just grasp in ordinary life.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.09,1:11:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we'll move on from childhood to the next level.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.23,1:11:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens after childhood?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.81,1:11:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens after childhood then is adolescence.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.48,1:11:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we can successfully come out of childhood then...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.64,1:11:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We come out into adolescence.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.64,1:11:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Where again we are in a world of world events.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.81,1:11:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either a dangerous world or a safe world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.81,1:11:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an emotional climate.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.84,1:11:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then adolescence financial adequacy of the family and yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.38,1:12:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The amount of social acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.53,1:12:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The education that you receive.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.06,1:12:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Your friends and comrades.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.47,1:12:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The emergence of sexuality and hormones.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.81,1:12:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And your preparation for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.81,1:12:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And here of course we're profoundly involved in heredity.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.97,1:12:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So the attitudes that we grow up with then are, as you can see, the result of a complex interaction of biologic and social and family, cultural and relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.75,1:12:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.75,1:12:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the next thing after you've been through that battering ramble.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.02,1:12:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That battering ramble of whammies.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.28,1:12:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You now become an adult.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.28,1:12:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.28,1:12:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the problems really start.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.38,1:12:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I going to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.38,1:12:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I going to be in this world?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.82,1:13:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I going to be getting married or be single?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.82,1:13:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I going to be heterosexual or homosexual?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.82,1:13:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I going to be part of a group?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.82,1:13:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I going to be isolated?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.82,1:13:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Marriage and the family become extremely important.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.82,1:13:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, adverse effects can happen to you in searching for success.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.34,1:13:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're all affected without our really being aware of it, of world conditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.72,1:13:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I tend to keep my eye on the news and periodically throughout the day catch up with world events.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.72,1:13:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because world conditions affect your own emotional attitudes and expectations without your being aware of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.72,1:13:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, well, that's all happening out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.72,1:13:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But out there is actually where you live.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.72,1:13:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Out there is really you can turn the TV set around and see that you are the out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.07,1:13:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, your health profoundly affects you and your financial situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.26,1:14:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Aging has its own profound effects on attitudes and your politics, political, your intellectual capacity and interests.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.55,1:14:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If your interests are in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.55,1:14:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're intellectually interested in the great books of the Western world, you will end up more philosophic and sophisticated.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.64,1:14:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the introvert versus the extrovert.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.86,1:14:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, we're all profoundly affected by our physical appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.00,1:14:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people like myself are good looking.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.35,1:14:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to fight off the women.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.50,1:14:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of us have to adjust to the fact that we are not looking like Hollywood.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.97,1:14:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.30,1:14:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But does happiness depend on that?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.30,1:14:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.30,1:14:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I've known some ugly, really ugly people.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.50,1:14:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They're hard to look at.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.81,1:14:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're extremely happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.81,1:15:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And some beautiful people, extremely miserable.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.42,1:15:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a psychiatrist, I saw them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.44,1:15:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Handsome young men have a negative self-image and should be out there and successful in every area.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.57,1:15:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Lovely women who...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.57,1:15:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to surmount.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.57,1:15:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the things that we have to surmount.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.57,1:15:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And by our spiritual evolution, we transcend these things which to other people are limitations.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.73,1:15:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't want anybody out there to have any limitations.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.73,1:15:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Cross out all limitations.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.10,1:15:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're an unlimited being.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.10,1:15:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're subject only to what you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.10,1:15:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're an unlimited being.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.26,1:15:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only subject to what you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.26,1:15:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think you're stupid and ugly, I got news for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.26,1:15:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're stupid and ugly.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.26,1:16:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think you're lovable, then you are lovable.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.76,1:16:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think you're not lovable, then you're not lovable.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.76,1:16:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So we really become that which we hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.76,1:16:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why we went through these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.76,1:16:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,These are things that people just take for granted without thinking about it, unless you're in psychoanalysis.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.76,1:16:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And have to lay there and discuss all these things with your analyst.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.85,1:16:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And the average person then has to surmount all these obstacles to fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.90,1:16:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And go through these obstacles in order to reach enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.10,1:16:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're interested primarily in reaching the levels of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.10,1:16:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore we want to successfully transcend all these stresses of ordinary life.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.10,1:16:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Good enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.06,1:16:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody for enlightenment?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.86,1:17:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So you work like a dog to reach enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.86,1:17:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you realize there's nobody to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.86,1:17:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought there was somebody or some individual that's going to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.85,1:17:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And you find out that that's fiction.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.85,1:17:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You wasted your life pursuing fiction.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.85,1:17:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That you're going to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.69,1:17:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you discover there is nobody to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.69,1:17:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What a relief.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.73,1:17:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody here has to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.73,1:17:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to buy into that goal of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.14,1:17:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, heck with enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.43,1:17:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to be stupid and ugly.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.25,1:17:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,To be happy if you're stupid and ugly means you're enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.34,1:17:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we're going to take a break for how long?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.34,1:17:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For about 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.34,1:17:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take a 15 minute break.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.34,1:18:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I want everybody to stay out of trouble for 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.89,1:18:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you stay out of trouble for 15 minutes?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.88,1:18:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the question.
